snippet.textDisplay: You know, some people consider president Jackson still being in office at the end a plot hole, but if you look closely it is clearly a critique of our political system. Just think about what President Jackson says when his plan is revealed, “Who do you think people will believe, the president? Or a man like this?” The American people are easy to forgive and forget the president’s wrongdoings, so Michael is saying that we don’t hold those in power accountable for their actions. The president is not held to a high standard, and in the end Scarn has to keep working with him because he is still president and holds power over him. Michael Scott clearly put thought into every aspect of this film, and there is no way it is just a simple plot hole, but rather a tragic consequence of the abuse of power.
